1. Quick Start
Copy LocalUserPwdMgr.exe to your USB drive.
Always Run as Administrator (Right-click -> Run as administrator).
On first run, set a Master Password (min. 10 characters).
2. Password Management
Select a user and use â€œGenerate Passwordâ€ for 2026-compliant security.
Click â€œApply Passwordâ€ to commit the change. The log is automatically stored in the protected session buffer.
3. Using the Sync Function (Security Note)
The Sync button should be used only if strictly necessary (e.g., if you need to immediately view newly created logs from another device without restarting the app).
DO NOT use Sync as a standard exit procedure. The script automatically handles data consolidation safely during the next startup to minimize corruption risks.
4. Safe USB Removal
To exit the program, use the â€œCloseâ€ button only.
After closing, use the Windows â€œSafely Remove Hardwareâ€ notification before physically unplugging the USB drive.
5. Local Group Management (New in v1.1)
5.1 Opening the Group Manager
Select a user from the main list.
Click Manage Groups.
A window will appear showing all local groups available on the system.
5.2 How the Interface Works
The list shows all local groups.
Groups where the user is already a member are preâ€‘checked.
You can check or uncheck groups to add or remove the user.
5.3 Applying Changes
When you click Apply:
The user is added to the groups you selected.
The user is removed from groups you unchecked.
A confirmation message appears once the update is complete.
5.4 Automatic Refresh
After closing the Group Manager:
The user list updates automatically.
The updated group memberships appear next to each username.
5.5 Logging
All group operations are recorded in the encrypted session buffer:
Added groups
Removed groups
Logs are merged into the main archive at the next application startup.

